title: [Gyldemar Forest, Ruined Road]
description: A pair of short retaining walls hold back the surrounding earth at the entry to the road.  The walls continue alongside the road as it winds to the southwest.  Sections of the walls have collapsed, spilling mounds of earth.

A pair of short retaining walls hold back the surrounding earth at the entry to the road.  The walls continue alongside the road as it winds to the southwest.  Sections of the walls have collapsed, spilling mounds of earth.  A number of nocturnal insects creep along the walls.
